<p><img src="../images/website-workflow.jpg" alt="workflow" /></p>

<p>The workflow for the website is fairly simple
There are two repos <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">dev</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">prod</code> 
GitHub Actions is setup on the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">dev</code> repository so when there are changes it would push to production at 12:00AM PDT</p>

<p>Below is an example code on how this is done:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>name: Sync changes to prod

on:
  schedule:
    - cron: '0 7 * * *'

jobs:
  sync:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    env:
      DEV_REPO: "dev.zoofytech.github.io"
      PROD_REPO: "zoofytech.github.io"
      USERNAME: "zoofytech"
    steps:
    - name: Checkout repository
      uses: actions/checkout@v2
      with:
        repository: $
        token: $

    - name: Check for changes
      run: |
        if ! git diff --exit-code HEAD HEAD~1; then
          exit 0
        fi

    - name: Push changes to other repository
      run: |
        git remote add other-repo https://x-access-token:$@github.com/$/.git
        git diff --name-only HEAD HEAD~1 | xargs -I{} git push other-repo HEAD:{} -f
        git log -1 --pretty=%B &gt; commit-message.txt
        git commit --amend -F commit-message.txt
</code></pre></div></div>
